#################### INSTALL JENKINS #####################
*launch ec2 instance
*google search "jenkins.io" click on "CenyOS/Fedore/RedHat"
*"sudo wget -O /etc/yum.repos.d/jenkins.repo https://pkg.jenkins.io/redhat-stable/jenkins.repo"
*"sudo rpm --import https://pkg.jenkins.io/redhat-stable/jenkins.io.key"
*"sudo yum install java-17-amazon-corretto-devel"
*"sudo yum install jenkins"
*"sudo systemctl start jenkins"

#################### CONFIGURE JENKINS ###################
*instance public ip:8080 in google
*"sudo cat /var/lib/jenkins/secrets/initialAdminPassword" copy this and paste in command promt
*copy the alphabetanumeric and paste
*"sudo systemctl enable jenkins" (this command use is when instance is rebooting automatically start jenkins)

############## JENKINS CREDINTIALS ######################
*"sudo yum install git"
*"git clone <project url>"

*dashboard - project - cofiguration - source code management - git - add credintials

